Reasoning: The paper deals with the design of online network coding algorithms for streaming applications with delay constraints. This involves the study of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI) to ensure timely delivery of data. The focus on perfect feedback and heterogeneous erasure probabilities suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of uncoded packets at key times for effective delay control may involve multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
